1) What you need installed (one-time)
A) Python

Install Python 3.10–3.12 (recommended for Kivy/KivyMD compatibility).

During install, check: ✅ Add Python to PATH

Verify:

python --version
pip --version
B) Git (optional but recommended)

Install Git so you can git clone repos.

Verify:

git --version
2) Get the project files
Option A: If you got a ZIP

Extract it

Find the folder that contains main.py (in your case looks like Sprint03\main.py)

Option B: If it’s on GitHub
git clone <repo_url>
cd <repo_folder>\Sprint03
3) Create a virtual environment (VERY IMPORTANT)

Go to the folder where main.py is:

cd C:\path\to\project\Sprint03
python -m venv venv

Activate it:

PowerShell
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

If PowerShell blocks it:

Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser RemoteSigned
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
CMD
venv\Scripts\activate

You should see (venv) in the terminal.

4) Install required libraries

Upgrade pip first:

python -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel

Install dependencies:

pip install kivy kivymd mysql-connector-python

If Kivy fails to install properly, use this (common Windows fix):

pip install "kivy[base]"
5) Make sure the folder structure is correct

Inside Sprint03, you should have something like:

main.py

admin_screen.py, billing_screen.py, etc.

database.py

helpers.py

instructionscrap.py

Image\QELogo.jpg

Image\GCashQR.jpg

Image\1.jpg ... 10.jpg

If images are missing, the app can still run, but you’ll see blank images / errors.

6) Run the app

From the same folder as main.py:

python main.py
7) Database setup (remote DB)

Your app connects to a remote MySQL. If you see:

Access denied for user ...
then the credentials/permissions are wrong OR the DB host blocks your IP.

What you can do:

Check that database.py has the correct host/user/password/db/port

If your database.py supports environment variables, set them before running, e.g.:

PowerShell (temporary for that terminal)
$env:DB_HOST="..."
$env:DB_USER="..."
$env:DB_PASSWORD="..."
$env:DB_NAME="..."
$env:DB_PORT="3306"
python main.py

(I’m not repeating any credentials here—treat DB passwords as secret.)

8) Common problems + quick fixes
A) “ModuleNotFoundError: kivy / kivymd / mysql”

You forgot to activate venv, or installed outside venv.
Fix:

.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install kivy kivymd mysql-connector-python
B) App opens then crashes / UI doesn’t update

Usually mismatch between code files being edited vs the one you’re running.
Fix: make sure your terminal cd is inside the folder with the correct main.py.

C) Kivy warnings about Image properties (allow_stretch, keep_ratio)

Not fatal. It’s just warning that those properties are deprecated.

D) Can’t connect to DB (1045 / access denied)

Not a code bug; it’s credentials/permissions/host restriction.
